 a
Vorst (including Karma rituals) usually take one and a half times longer th=
an
normal to complete. Certain commonsense exceptions to this rule apply: they
cast spells during combat as quickly as possible, for instance, but many ot=
her
opportunities for roleplaying this Vorst characteristic will arise during p=
lay.
Players and gamemasters should use Vorst zealousness as a roleplaying tool,
however, and not allow it to impede the flow of the game.</p>

