<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Obsidimen poss=
ess
the following racial abilities:</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Increased Wound
Threshold: Add +3 to the Wound Threshold of obsidimen to represent this rac=
e‚Äôs
inherent resistance to damage from their stone-like skin.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Natural Armor:
Obsidimen have very tough skin, which serves them as armor. Obsidiman skin =
has
a Physical Armor Rating of 3. Obsidimen can only wear other types of living
armor, which add their protection to the character‚Äôs Natural Armor. (See =
Armor
and Shields, p. 254; types of armor considered ‚Äúliving‚Äù are indicated a=
s such
in the armor‚Äôs description.)</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Listen to the =
rocks
of the earth. Those around you want to hurry, for they listen to the waters=
 of
their blood and the fire of their hearts. You are hewn from living rock. Li=
sten
to the rocks of the earth. The call of those around you is the call of the =
volcano.
The fire of other hearts burns hot enough to melt your world around you. Li=
sten
to the rocks of the earth.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>‚ÄîSaying from=
 The
Liferock, dwarf translation</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-size:11.0pt'><span style=3D'font-family:Wingdin=
