fearsome sight when angered‚Äîwhich their elongated lower canines serve to
enhance. They anger quickly indeed, due to a feature known as gahad. An ork=
‚Äôs
gahad is an individual reflex unique to each ork that can be awoken by some=
one
else saying or doing ‚Äúthat one wrong thing‚Äù in the ork‚Äôs presence, an=
d the ork
can either give in to it, be driven to resolve the situation, or try to
restrain himself. While inconvenient for other races, orks consider gahad a=
s a
sign of being alive, an energy from deep within that burns as the heart pou=
nds
