<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Tail Combat:
T‚Äôskrang often make use of their tails when engaged in combat. A t‚Äôskra=
ng can
use his tail to whip at opponents in unarmed combat much like striking with=
 an
arm or kicking with a leg, using an appropriate unarmed combat talent or sk=
ill
for any Attack Tests. The Damage Step used is the character‚Äôs Strength St=
ep,
unless modified by abilities that enhance unarmed combat Damage. A t‚Äôskra=
ng may
also latch a melee weapon of up to Size 2 to his tail, and this is treated =
as
an Attached Weapon (see p. 248). Tail Combat allows t‚Äôskrang to use the C=
ombat
Options of Tail Attack and Tail Parry (see p. 226).</p>

