<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Like jungle
t‚Äôskrang, Pale Ones rely on relatively primitive weapons and armor, but p=
ick up
the use of swords and knives quickly. Pale Ones gain Heat Sight (Player‚Äôs
Guide, p. 20) as an additional Racial Ability.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Winged T‚Äôskr=
ang</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Most k‚Äôstula=
ami, or
winged t‚Äôskrang, born to the t‚Äôskrang society of the Serpent River leav=
e their
homes around the time they become adults at age 12. The k‚Äôstulaami are bo=
rn
with a passion to fly that consumes their nature, even changing their langu=
age.
The Serpent River t‚Äôskrang find these t‚Äôskrang difficult to live with a=
nd
understand, and so it is that most k‚Äôstulaami find their way to a large
community of their kind that lives in the Throal Mountains. These t‚Äôskrang
rarely choose to travel across Barsaive and live among the other Namegivers,
