rom
twenty to five minutes, and the Difficulty Number of the Toughness Tests
increases by +2 every minute, instead of every five minutes. When flying wi=
th
wet wings, the windling is considered Harried (see p. 227). Windling wings =
dry
within ten minutes of being in a dry place, or within five minutes of being=
 in
a warm place, such as in front of an open fire.</p>

